          <msContents>
            <summary>
              <p>57 fol.; Writing surface: parchment; Shelfmark: H. S. 184; Text: Q 44:38-Q 53:58; 10 lines per page; Dimensions: 197 x 140 mm; Script style: kūfī; Estimated date of production: 2nd (8th) to 3rd (9th) centuries [according to Karatay]. </p>
              <p>This entry is based on the catalogue of Fehmi E. Karatay (1888-1968). Currently we do not have access to the images. With exceptions, the catalogue does not contain precise information on the distribution of the text throughout the pages. For this reason, only fol. 1 is given. </p>
              <p><ref target="https://www.zotero.org/groups/corpuscoranicum_pub/items/itemKey/UEN2FUP7" sameAs="UEN2FUP7" type="zotero">Karatay (1962)</ref> describes the manuscripts as follows, p. 6: "16 H. S. 184 Kur’an’dan bir bölüm Parşömen. 140mm boy ve 197mm eninde cönk şeklinde 57 yaprak. Sahifede kûfî ile 135mm uzunl.[uğunda] 10 satır. Takriben II - III. asırda yazılmıştır. Bu parça Duḫan (44) suresinin 38. ayeti ile başlayıp Nacm (53) suresinin 58. ayetinin sonunda bitmektedir."</p>
              <p>This can be translated as follows: "16 H. S. 184 A part of the Qurʾān Parchment. 57 leaves of 140 mm height and 197 mm width. The text area written in Kufic script [contains] 10 lines measuring 135 mm. Approximately copied during 2nd-3rd [(8th-9th)] centuries. The codex begins with Q 44:38 (Sūra al-Duḫān) and ends at the ed of Q 53:58 (Sūra al-Najm)."</p>
            </summary>
